{
  "stem": "13469.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We could write letters and postcards, and again, I have samples of those that my parents wrote to non-Jewish friends in Amsterdam and elsewhere in Holland.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we recovered these letters after the war-- they gave them back to us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I have all those documentary evidence of where we were, and which barracks we lived in, in Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And what we asked for-- we-- my parents seemed to ask for syrup, which is a cough mixture, quite a lot.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In one letter they asked for pajamas, and in another letter for various other things.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we-- we were allowed to have food parcels and clothing parcels and all those things in Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So all in all, it wasn't really all that bad.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The other thing we have, which is peculiar-- and not many people seem to have all these documents.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "In fact, I've never seen anybody else who has these documents-- is my [NON-ENGLISH] which is the bath card.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And it shows that I had to have a bath at Friday afternoon, at 3 o'clock, every week.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And not only was that regulated-- so there was a bath house, and I had to report there 3 o'clock every Friday afternoon-- but it got stamped.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "The card was stamped on the back on the 1st of January, on the 14th of January, the 7th of January, the 21st of January, 1944.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The card was stamped every time to say that I had my bath properly.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And my family after the war were very impressed to hear I had a bath every week, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was better than I do nowadays, really.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know what they were.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I wouldn't have thought so-- no, I think we went into individual tubs, or maybe there were showers.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
